TY  - JOUR
AU  - Aiyagari, S. Rao
T1  - Can There Be Short-Period Deterministic Cycles When People Are Long Lived?*
PY  - 1989
Y1  - 1989/02/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937839
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 104
IS  - 1
SP  - 163
EP  - 185
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper considers whether short-period deterministic cycles can exist in a class of stationary overlapping generations models with long- (but finite-) lived agents. It shows that if agents discount the future positively, then as life spans get large, nonmonetary cycles will disappear. Further, neither constant monetary steady states nor stationary monetary cycles can exist. It also shows that if agents discount the future negatively, then there are robust examples in which constant monetary steady states as well as stationary monetary cycles (with undiminished amplitude) can occur no matter how long agents live.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937839
ER  - 



